               <head>Hebrew-Latin dictionary</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85059886" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A Hebrew-Latin dictionary.</summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="la"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85059886">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="56v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Milon ῾ivri-latini</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">מלון עברי-לטיני</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The manuscript contains: the letters shin and tav of a Hebrew and Latin vocabulary, excerpted from Buxtorf's Lexicon Hebreaicum et Chaldaicum (folio 1r); the double signification of several verbal forms (folio 27r); "variae et incertae originis vocabula" (folio 28r); duties of husband and wife, from Ex. 21:10, followed by a list of Hebrew words signifying rain and storm (folio 31r); list of words substituted by the "scribae masorethae" for unaesthetic expressions in the Bible (folio 32r); a classed list of Hebrew words and phrases (folio 32v); a list of majuscular, suspended and inveerted letters (folio 37v); "gemmae, lapides pretiosi" (folio 39r); notes on ancient coins and measures, with an appendix on English measures (folio 44r).</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>A number of leaves have been left blank before folio 44r.</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
